1) Imagine the gem, what is the user experience?
2) Start with project structure (i.e., files) -- use Google
3) Start with entry point, the file run
4) Force that to build the CLI interface
5) Stub out interface (i.e., make fake objects)
6) Make things real
7) Discover objects -- one object does one thing
8) Program -- broken, working, refactor, broken, working.... etc

A command line interface program, Brews Near You.

User types Find Brews

Program welcomes user and asks for postal code

User types postal code

Program returns a numbered list of breweries with name, street address, and primary product(?)

Program asks user to select a brewery from the list to learn more about

User types number

Program returns detailed information on the brewery